Description: Comfort Line manufactures a patented clothing solution for people living with a central line or port catheter.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Baltimore-Maryland Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Comfort Line manufactures a patented clothing solution for people living with a central line or port catheter. This garment design addresses an overlooked need for people living with these medical devices. Currently, the most common practice for securing a central line is to tape the device directly to the skin or safety pin it to the person’s shirt. These methods of securing a central line can cause skin sores, inadvertent damage to the device or potential infection. The primary goals of Comfort Line garments are to help prevent causes of device damage, medical complications and infection. Comfort Line apparel is sensitive to both the needs of individuals and medical providers dealing with central line maintenance, care, and safety. Comfort Line was issued U.S. Patent No.8,607,366 B2 for its medical garment design and is actively working with several nationally recognized medical centers in pediatric oncology.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Ether2 is in the business of designing, manufacturing, selling, and licensing technology for ubiquitous network communications. This remarkable (Layer 2) switching technology eliminates the need for complicated routers, switches and middle hardware whose job it is to create an asynchronous network on top of a synchronous network. Ether2 enables synchronous circuits to be efficiently shared by thousands of users transmitting Ethernet and Internet Protocol (IP) packets. Companies using Ether2 technology are able to provide a superior level of service that comingles packet and fixed-bandwidth offerings, using only their already installed synchronous infrastructure — no routers and no software changes. The benefits of an Ether2 Distributed Q network will be seen in LAN / WAN / MAN environments, including all wireless applications from WiFi to cellular to satellite.

Description: Mobile SaaS platform for speech-language pathologists and their patients with neurological disorders
Full Description: At Cortex, we're developing a mobile platform that provides supplemental therapy activities for speech-language pathologists (SLPs) and their patients who suffer from a neurological disorder, such as a stroke, traumatic brain injury, or Alzheimer's Disease.  Currently, 65.4 million Americans suffer from one of these disorders, yet only 22 million receive the SLP treatment that they so desperately need, costing the healthcare industry nearly $20 billion in 2016 alone.  With the geriatric population expected to increase 50% (from 50 to 75 million) by 2030, the American healthcare industry will become increasingly overwhelmed due to a lack in human capital output (despite SLP job growth projected at nearly 20%).  Furthermore, a significant gap in therapy is created whenever a patient is discharged from their SLP, as they no longer have access to their activity regimen.  This absence of therapy regularly leads to cognitive and functional decline, resulting in one of five patients readmitting back to the hospital within the first thirty days of discharge.  Cortex solves this problem by providing dynamic and highly personalized therapy activities right on your mobile device.  By increasing therapy frequency and quality, Cortex may significantly increase the patient's progress (during therapy), therapy maintenance (after discharge), and the overall quality of life for everyone involved -- all the while driving down healthcare costs due to needless re-hospitilizations.
